# First Question

## What is Spark Structured Streaming?

Most beginners think:

> Spark Streaming processes one record at a time.

❌ Not exactly.

Spark Structured Streaming uses **micro-batches**.

---

Imagine Kafka receives:

```text id="jshmym"
Message 1
Message 2
Message 3
Message 4
Message 5
```

Spark groups them:

```text id="40o07w"
Batch 1
 ├─ Message 1
 ├─ Message 2
 └─ Message 3

Batch 2
 ├─ Message 4
 └─ Message 5
```

and processes them together.

---

# Why Not Process One Event At A Time?

Processing:

```text id="57pq8s"
1 event
1 event
1 event
1 event
```

creates huge overhead.

Micro-batching gives:

✅ Better throughput

✅ Lower cost

✅ Easier fault recovery

---

# Interview Question

### Is Spark Structured Streaming truly real-time?

Strong answer:

> Spark Structured Streaming is near real-time because it processes data in micro-batches rather than processing every event individually.

